pokemon1.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon1.description: Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun's rays, the seed grows progressively larger.

pokemon2.name: Ivysaur
pokemon2.description: There is a bud on this Pokémon's back. To support its weight, Ivysaur's legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it starts spending more time lying in the sunlight, it's a sign that the bud will bloom into a large flower soon.

pokemon3.name: Venusaur
pokemon3.description: There is a large flower on Venusaur's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.

pokemon4.name: Charmander
pokemon4.description: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is enjoying itself. If the Pokémon becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely.

pokemon5.name: Charmeleon
pokemon5.description: Charmeleon mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. If it encounters a strong foe, it turns aggressive. In this excited state, the flame at the tip of its tail flares with a bluish white color.

pokemon6.name: Charizard
pokemon6.description: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.

pokemon7.name: Squirtle
pokemon7.description: Squirtle's shell is not merely used for protection. The shell's rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, enabling this Pokémon to swim at high speeds.

pokemon8.name: Wartortle
pokemon8.description: Its tail is large and covered with a rich, thick fur. The tail becomes increasingly deeper in color as Wartortle ages. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness as a battler.

pokemon9.name: Blastoise
pokemon9.description: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

pokemon10.name: Caterpie
pokemon10.description: Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor.

pokemon11.name: Metapod
pokemon11.description: The shell covering this Pokémon's body is as hard as an iron slab. Metapod does not move very much. It stays still because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the hard shell.

pokemon12.name: Butterfree
pokemon12.description: Butterfree has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.

pokemon13.name: Weedle
pokemon13.description: Weedle has an extremely acute sense of smell. It is capable of distinguishing its favorite kinds of leaves from those it dislikes just by sniffing with its big red proboscis (nose).

pokemon14.name: Kakuna
pokemon14.description: Kakuna remains virtually immobile as it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it is extremely busy as it prepares for its coming evolution. This is evident from how hot the shell becomes to the touch.

pokemon15.name: Beedrill
pokemon15.description: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest—this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.

pokemon16.name: Pidgey
pokemon16.description: Pidgey has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It is capable of unerringly returning home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.

pokemon17.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon17.description: Pidgeotto claims a large area as its own territory. This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its living space. If its territory is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.

pokemon18.name: Pidgeot
pokemon18.description: This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.

pokemon19.name: Rattata
pokemon19.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

pokemon20.name: Raticate
pokemon20.description: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

pokemon21.name: Rattata
pokemon21.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

pokemon22.name: Fearow
pokemon22.description: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

pokemon23.name: Ekans
pokemon23.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

pokemon24.name: Arbok
pokemon24.description: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

pokemon25.name: Pikachu
pokemon25.description: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

pokemon26.name: Raichu
pokemon26.description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

pokemon27.name: Sandshrew
pokemon27.description: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

pokemon28.name: Sandslash
pokemon28.description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

pokemon29.name: Nidoran
pokemon29.description: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

pokemon30.name: Nidorina
pokemon30.description: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting

pokemon31.name: Nidoqueen
pokemon31.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

pokemon32.name: Nidoran
pokemon32.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

pokemon33.name: Nidorino
pokemon33.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

pokemon34.name: Nidoking
pokemon34.description: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

pokemon35.name: Clefairy
pokemon35.description: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

pokemon36.name: Clefable
pokemon36.description: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

pokemon37.name: Vulpix
pokemon37.description: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

pokemon38.name: Ninetales
pokemon38.description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

pokemon39.name: Jigglypuff
pokemon39.description: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

pokemon40.name: Wigglytuff
pokemon40.description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

pokemon41.name: Zubat
pokemon41.description: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

pokemon42.name: Golbat
pokemon42.description: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

pokemon43.name: Oddish
pokemon43.description: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

pokemon44.name: Gloom
pokemon44.description: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

pokemon45.name: Vileplume
pokemon45.description: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

pokemon46.name: Paras
pokemon46.description: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

pokemon47.name: Parasect
pokemon47.description: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

pokemon48.name: Venonat
pokemon48.description: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

pokemon49.name: Venomoth
pokemon49.description: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

pokemon50.name: Diglett
pokemon50.description: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

pokemon51.name: Dugtrio
pokemon51.description: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

pokemon52.name: Meowth
pokemon52.description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

pokemon53.name: Persian
pokemon53.description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

pokemon54.name: Psyduck
pokemon54.description: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

pokemon55.name: Golduck
pokemon55.description: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

pokemon56.name: Mankey
pokemon56.description: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

pokemon57.name: Primeape
pokemon57.description: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

pokemon58.name: Growlithe
pokemon58.description: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

pokemon59.name: Arcanine
pokemon59.description: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

pokemon60.name: Poliwag
pokemon60.description: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

pokemon61.name: Poliwhirl
pokemon61.description: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

pokemon62.name: Poliwrath
pokemon62.description: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

pokemon63.name: Abra
pokemon63.description: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

pokemon64.name: Kadabra
pokemon64.description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

pokemon65.name: Alakazam
pokemon65.description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

pokemon66.name: Machop
pokemon66.description: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

pokemon67.name: Machoke
pokemon67.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

pokemon68.name: Machamp
pokemon68.description: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

pokemon69.name: Bellsprout
pokemon69.description: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

pokemon70.name: Weepinbell
pokemon70.description: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

pokemon71.name: Victreebel
pokemon71.description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

pokemon72.name: Tentacool
pokemon72.description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

pokemon73.name: Tentacruel
pokemon73.description: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

pokemon74.name: Geodude
pokemon74.description: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

pokemon75.name: Graveler
pokemon75.description: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.
